  • 【R】kerasを使ったディープラーニングがお手軽すぎる！

パッケージインストール

library(keras)
x = t(sapply(1:1000,function(i){
  if(i <500){
    rnorm(2,1)
  }else{
    rnorm(2,-1)
  }
}))

y = c(rep(1,500),rep(0,500))
y = to_categorical(y,2)
plot(x[,1],x[,2],col=y+2)

typeof(x)
## [1] "double"
typeof(y)
## [1] "double"
dim(x)
## [1] 1000    2
dim(y)
## [1] 1000    2
model = keras_model_sequential()
model %>%
  layer_dense(units=16,activation="relu",input_shape = c(dim(x)[2])) %>%
  layer_dropout(rate=0.4) %>%
  layer_dense(units=8,activation="relu") %>%
  layer_dropout(rate=0.3) %>%
  layer_dense(units=2,activation = "softmax")
model %>% compile(
  loss = "categorical_crossentropy",
  optimizer = optimizer_rmsprop(),
  metrics = c("accuracy")
)
model %>% fit(x,y,
              epochs = 100,batch_size = 100,validation_split = 0.2)
x = t(sapply(1:1000,function(i){
  runif(2,min=-2,max=2)
}))
y = model %>% predict(x)

plot(x[,1],x[,2],col=apply(y,1,which.min)+1)
